<item>
            <title>[LU-102] EXPORT_SYMBOL of static function breaks compile</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-102</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t know exactly when gcc started catching this, but:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;gcc 4.4.4 in RHEL6 on ppc64 does not allow EXPORT_SYMBOL for&lt;br/&gt;
a static function (which seems reasonable). The following error&lt;br/&gt;
is seen on the EXPORT_SYMBOL line:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;error: __ksymtab_obd_device_alloc causes a section type conflict&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is simply to remove the EXPORT_SYMBOL line, which I think is fine.  I can&apos;t find anywhere else that references that symbol outside of that one file.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch is here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/262&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/262&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>RHEL6, PPC64</environment>
